# Generate Commit Guidelines

When the user asks for a commit, use this format.

## Types

- `fix:` — bug fix (PATCH)
- `feat:` — new feature (MINOR)
- Also allowed: `chore:`, `docs:`, `style:`, `refactor:`, `perf:`, `test:`, etc.

Optional scope in parentheses: `feat(hero): add entrance animation`

## Subject and body

- Format: `<type>[optional scope]: <description>`
- **Imperative mood** in the subject (e.g. `add`, `fix`, `update`).
- **No period** at the end of the subject line.
- Use the body to explain **what** and **why**, not step-by-step how.

## Examples

```
feat(hero): add Motion entrance animation

Improve first paint perception on the landing section without layout shift.
```

```
fix(nav): restore keyboard focus trap on mobile menu
```
